title: Supra® - Greater Springfield Board of Realtors

contentTree.content:
Supra® Keys & Lockboxes

Supra is the leading global provider of key management solutions. REALTORS® across the country utilize SUPRA lockboxes for convenient, secure house showings.

About Supra®

Supra released its first lockbox system in 1955 for the real estate industry. The Supra real estate lockbox system is managed today by real estate associations and Multiple Listing Services for real estate agents to efficiently market and show listed homes.

The Supra System makes it easy for showing agents to access properties and for listing agents to track activity at client properties. The latest Supra® keybox, iBox BT LE, adds Bluetooth® Low Energy technology, and communicates with newer smartphones without any additional hardware. A data record is created each time a keybox is opened, and Supra’s wireless keys transmit the showing information immediately so real estate agents can obtain real-time information about showings. Client questions can be answered quickly, and feedback from showing agents can be gathered while information is fresh in the showing agent’s and client’s minds.

Based in Salem, Oregon, USA, Supra is part of UTC Climate, Controls & Security, a unit of United Technologies Corporation.

Keys

Supra electronic keys can be a proprietary electronic device or an eKEY® application running on popular smartphones. All the Supra keys include PIN-code security. The keys record events each time a keybox is opened.

Key Boxes

Supra electronic keyboxes have been used on millions of homes. Current models of keyboxes can be opened using Bluetooth® or infrared signals. Supra’s system records events each time a keybox is opened.

Download Supra® eKEY App
Supra® FAQs
Access
How do I obtain Supra access?

Only members who hold MLS membership through our Association, or *Affiliate Keyholder membership may obtain a key. Unlicensed Assistants will not be issued a key.

Is there an activation fee?
Can I add or cancel my Supra at any time?
Can I be assigned more than one key on multiple devices?
Lockboxes
Where do I get new lockboxes?

New lockboxes may be leased from the Association.

How much are new lockboxes?
Can I purchase “used” boxes?
How much are “used” boxes?
What happens if my lockbox is missing or stolen?
Is a lockbox required on all listings?
What happens if my lockbox malfunctions?
What do I do if my lockbox is unresponsive?
How do I assign a lockbox to my listing?
How do I stop receiving showing notifications on a lockbox?
Compatible Devices
What operating systems are supported with the new eKey app?

The refreshed eKEY app requires Android™ OS 5 or greater or Apple® iOS 10 or greater.

What if I don’t have the necessary operating system on my phone? Will the system let me keep my old eKEY app?
Apple Watch®
Does the one-day PIN work on the Apple Watch?

Yes, when “Only Require PIN Once Per Day” is enabled in the eKEY app settings.

Can the eKEY app on the Apple Watch work independently of the iPhone®?
How close does the Apple Watch need to be to the iPhone to use the eKEY app?
If the Apple Watch is paired with the iPhone, is the eKEY app authorized on both devices simultaneously?
Android™ Watch
Are there any plans for any Android watches to be compatible with the eKEY app?

Not at this time. The team is reviewing the technical requirements.

Biometrics
If I set the eKEY app to require biometrics to open the key container, will I still have to enter the PIN code?
Yes, enabling biometrics provides a two-factor authentication.
To limit the PIN entry to once per day, turn on “Only Require PIN Once Per Day” in eKEY Settings.
If the once per day PIN code is enabled in the eKEY app and biometrics are turned off, could anyone pick up my phone and use it to open keyboxes for the rest of the day?
Data at the Door
How is Supra accessing the Data at the Door information?

The information is composed of data supplied by the Association/MLS and the listing agent.

What message is displayed in the eKEY app if it is not connected to cellular service when the key container is opened?
Is the MLS number automatically added or does it need to be entered manually?
Messages
Can all messages be cleared at once or do they need to be opened individually?

Messages on iOS devices can be deleted from the list by swiping left. Messages for both iOS and Android can be deleted by viewing the message details and selecting delete.

Disclaimer

New Members are given the opportunity to get set up with a Supra Key/Lockbox during their new member appointment. 

Members who have Supra related questions or concerns should contact Supra support at: 1-877-699-6787 or send an email to: suprasupport@fs.utc.com.

Supra® Keys & Lockboxes

Supra is the leading global provider of key management solutions. REALTORS® across the country utilize SUPRA lockboxes for convenient, secure house showings.

About Supra®

Supra released its first lockbox system in 1955 for the real estate industry. The Supra real estate lockbox system is managed today by real estate associations and Multiple Listing Services for real estate agents to efficiently market and show listed homes.

The Supra System makes it easy for showing agents to access properties and for listing agents to track activity at client properties. The latest Supra® keybox, iBox BT LE, adds Bluetooth® Low Energy technology, and communicates with newer smartphones without any additional hardware. A data record is created each time a keybox is opened, and Supra’s wireless keys transmit the showing information immediately so real estate agents can obtain real-time information about showings. Client questions can be answered quickly, and feedback from showing agents can be gathered while information is fresh in the showing agent’s and client’s minds.

Based in Salem, Oregon, USA, Supra is part of UTC Climate, Controls & Security, a unit of United Technologies Corporation.

Keys

Supra electronic keys can be a proprietary electronic device or an eKEY® application running on popular smartphones. All the Supra keys include PIN-code security. The keys record events each time a keybox is opened.

Key Boxes

Supra electronic keyboxes have been used on millions of homes. Current models of keyboxes can be opened using Bluetooth® or infrared signals. Supra’s system records events each time a keybox is opened.

Download Supra® eKEY App

Supra® FAQs

Access

How do I obtain Supra access?

Only members who hold MLS membership through our Association, or *Affiliate Keyholder membership may obtain a key. Unlicensed Assistants will not be issued a key.

Is there an activation fee?

Yes, Supra eKEY activation fee is $50.00 plus tax, and Supra XpressKey® activation fee is $70.00 plus tax.

Can I add or cancel my Supra at any time?

Yes, you may cancel anytime by contacting support@gsbor.com.

Can I be assigned more than one key on multiple devices?

No, only one key may be issued.

Lockboxes

Where do I get new lockboxes?

New lockboxes may be leased from the Association.

How much are new lockboxes?

New lockboxes are $105.00 plus tax. Credit, debit, or check are accepted.

Can I purchase “used” boxes?

Yes, the Association occasionally has “used” boxes.

How much are “used” boxes?

Prices vary as they are set by the previous leaseholder. Exact cash or check are accepted.

What happens if my lockbox is missing or stolen?

Report it to the Association at support@gsbor.com.

Is a lockbox required on all listings?

If a lockbox is placed on a listing in Greene, Christian, and Webster county, it is required to be a Supra lockbox.

What happens if my lockbox malfunctions?

Return the box to the Association for replacement.

What do I do if my lockbox is unresponsive?

Visit the Supra Unresponsive Keybox page.

How do I assign a lockbox to my listing?
  1. From Flexmls go to the Change Listing menu and select Supra functions in the General column.
  2. Complete the lockbox serial number and shackle code fields.
  3. Then click the +Assign button. This assigns the lockbox to the listing both in Supra and in Flexmls.
How do I stop receiving showing notifications on a lockbox?
  1. Remove the lockbox from your eKEY by selecting the serial number in My Keyboxes. 
  2. Select “Program Keybox,” and then use the Delete button on the bottom left of the screen.

Compatible Devices

What operating systems are supported with the new eKey app?

The refreshed eKEY app requires Android™ OS 5 or greater or Apple® iOS 10 or greater.

What if I don’t have the necessary operating system on my phone? Will the system let me keep my old eKEY app?

App stores are smart enough to know which operating system you have and what is needed by the apps. Older devices that are not able to support the refreshed eKEY app will not be able to download the new app in the app store.

Apple Watch®

Does the one-day PIN work on the Apple Watch?

Yes, when “Only Require PIN Once Per Day” is enabled in the eKEY app settings.

Can the eKEY app on the Apple Watch work independently of the iPhone®?

No, the eKEY app on the Apple Watch can only be used if it’s in proximity of an iPhone.

How close does the Apple Watch need to be to the iPhone to use the eKEY app?

The Apple Watch must be within 30 feet of the iPhone.

If the Apple Watch is paired with the iPhone, is the eKEY app authorized on both devices simultaneously?

The Apple Watch works as a remote for the iPhone. As long as the Apple Watch is within 30 feet of the iPhone, it has the ability to open the key container, designate the showing ended (if end of showing is enabled), and send alert messages (if alert is activated for the organization).

Android™ Watch

Are there any plans for any Android watches to be compatible with the eKEY app?

Not at this time. The team is reviewing the technical requirements.

Biometrics

If I set the eKEY app to require biometrics to open the key container, will I still have to enter the PIN code?
    1. Yes, enabling biometrics provides a two-factor authentication.
    2. To limit the PIN entry to once per day, turn on “Only Require PIN Once Per Day” in eKEY Settings.
If the once per day PIN code is enabled in the eKEY app and biometrics are turned off, could anyone pick up my phone and use it to open keyboxes for the rest of the day?

The once per day PIN can only be enabled if your phone has a lock function turned on so that it requires a password, PIN, symbol, biometrics, etc. to access any apps on your phone. Trying to enable this feature without one of those security measures in place will prompt the user to enable a lock function in the settings of their phone.

Data at the Door

How is Supra accessing the Data at the Door information?

The information is composed of data supplied by the Association/MLS and the listing agent.

What message is displayed in the eKEY app if it is not connected to cellular service when the key container is opened?

The eKey app will display this message: “Unable to load listing details. Make sure you are connected to the Internet.”

Is the MLS number automatically added or does it need to be entered manually?
  1. The keybox needs to be assigned to a listing for Data at the Door to display. If the keybox is not assigned to a listing, there will not be any listing data displayed.
  2. If the listing has not been entered into the MLS yet, there will not be any listing data displayed.

Messages

Can all messages be cleared at once or do they need to be opened individually?

Messages on iOS devices can be deleted from the list by swiping left. Messages for both iOS and Android can be deleted by viewing the message details and selecting delete.

Disclaimer

New Members are given the opportunity to get set up with a Supra Key/Lockbox during their new member appointment. 

Members who have Supra related questions or concerns should contact Supra support at: 1-877-699-6787 or send an email to: suprasupport@fs.utc.com.
